# TiltCheck Core Guardrails

- Keep changes small and task-scoped; avoid broad refactors unless requested.
- Never commit secrets, tokens, private keys, or production credential values.
- Preserve OSS/runtime boundary; do not expose private runtime internals.
- For risky areas (`auth`, payments, trust scoring, external APIs), include:
  - threat/risk notes
  - validation/sanitization notes
  - rollback notes if behavior regresses
- Prefer targeted tests/validation for touched code paths before finishing.
- Do not revert unrelated user changes in a dirty worktree.

## Quick pass/fail check

- [ ] No secret or private runtime leakage
- [ ] Scope is focused and reversible
- [ ] Risky changes include verification notes
